[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: aa5f725795b842b8[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer-based fuzzer run against an RTF parsing component triggered a [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhigh-severity security finding [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe exception indicates that untrusted RTF-embedded object data is being [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialized without restriction, potentially allowing an attacker to instantiate [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marbitrary classes on the classpath and achieve remote code execution.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Overview  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The fuzzer input caused an exception in the deserialization logic invoked by the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRTF parser. The security framework [0m[1;39m([0m[39mJazzer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m flagged this as a remote code execution[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrisk due to unrestricted class or object creation from externally controlled data.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Deserialization-based Remote Code Execution: untrusted data is fed into [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mjava.io.ObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, enabling instantiation of arbitrary [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclasses if they exist on the classpath.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack Trace Highlights  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `jaz.Zer.reportFinding` → security report trigger  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `jaz.Zer.readObject` → custom deserialization wrapper  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `java.io.ObjectInputStream.readObject` → core deserialization  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject` → deserialization of embedded RTF [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobjects  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `TextExtractor.processGroupEnd` and `RTFParser.parseInline/parse` → parsing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpipeline  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. `com.example.RTFParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput` → fuzz harness entry point[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important Observations  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The vulnerable code path resides in the RTF embedding handler where embedded [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOLE objects are deserialized directly.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The issue is detected in the context of Apache Tika’s RTF parser, specifically [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munder the `microsoft.rtf` package.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness invoking `RTFParserFuzzer` is simply triggering this path [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand is not itself the root cause.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject`  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.TextExtractor` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mespecially [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`processGroupEnd`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFParser` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmethods `parseInline`, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`parse`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Any utility or wrapper around `ObjectInputStream` used for RTF-embedded data  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis review covers all relevant details of the finding without speculating on [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderlying causes or proposing remediations.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[39m:                Object obj = new [0m[1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m216[0m[39m:                        [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mUnsynchronizedByteArrayInputStream.builder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.setByteArray[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m217[0m[39m:                                [0m[1;35m.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m218[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS, [0m[1;35mobj.getClass[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview of the Root Cause  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The `[0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method unconditionally calls [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   `new [0m[1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when in the `JAVA_OBJDATA` state. This[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallows untrusted RTF-embedded Java serialized data to instantiate arbitrary [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclasses, leading to remote code execution.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. High-Level Fix  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Disable or sandbox Java object deserialization by default. Introduce a toggle [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflag [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdisabled by default[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that prevents consuming raw Java serialized streams. If [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man advanced user explicitly opts into “allowEmbeddedJavaObjects,” they assume RCE [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrisk; otherwise the parser should record and skip these embedded Java objects [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrather than deserializing them.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Steps to Implement the Patch  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Extend RTFParser to carry a new boolean configuration:  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • In `org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFParser`, add:  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        @Field  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private boolean allowEmbeddedJavaObjects = false;  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public void [0m[1;35msetAllowEmbeddedJavaObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean v[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis.allowEmbeddedJavaObjects = v; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public boolean [0m[1;35mgetAllowEmbeddedJavaObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m return [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowEmbeddedJavaObjects; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • In `[0m[1;35mparseInline[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, pass this flag into the handler:  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        RTFEmbObjHandler embObjHandler =  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            new [0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler[0m[1;39m([0m[39mhandler, metadata, context, [0m[1;35mgetMemoryLimitInKb[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowEmbeddedJavaObjects[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Modify the constructor and field of RTFEmbObjHandler:  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Add a private `final boolean allowJavaDeserialization;`  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Update its constructor signature to accept the new flag and assign it.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Harden [0m[1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for JAVA_OBJDATA:  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      Replace the direct call to `[0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with:  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!allowJavaDeserialization[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Security: skip untrusted Java serialization  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            TikaException e = new [0m[1;35mTikaException[0m[1;39m([0m[39m  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[32m"Embedded Java object deserialization is disabled for security"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mEmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException[0m[1;39m([0m[39me, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return;  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m OPTIONAL [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfuture[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: if [0m[33mallowJavaDeserialization[0m[39m==true, wrap OIS with an [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mObjectInputFilter  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ObjectInputStream ois = new [0m[1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Example JDK9+ API, enforce a minimal whitelist of safe classes  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m ObjectInputFilter filter = …;  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35msetObjectInputFilter[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfilter[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        Object obj = [0m[1;35mois.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        …  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Document Behavior & Tests  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Update the Javadoc of RTFParser to note that embedded Java objects are [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mignored unless `[0m[33mallowEmbeddedJavaObjects[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m`.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Add a unit test: feed minimal RTF with a `\javaobjdata` group, assert that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno deserialization occurs and that an exception is recorded via [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`EmbeddedDocumentUtil`.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Verify existing tests for OLE objects [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`objdata`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and images [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pict`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinue functioning unchanged.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Functionality  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – All other embedded-object flows [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`objdata`, `pict`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain untouched.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – By default the parser still handles OLE streams and images as before.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – The new flag is off by default, preserving the current behavior except [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblocking the previously unprotected Java-object path.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Security and Side Effects  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Side effect: real RTF content embedding serialized Java objects will now be [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mskipped instead of deserialized. This is acceptable since serialized Java objects [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare rare in typical documents and pose high risk.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Advanced users who legitimately require this feature can set [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[33mallowEmbeddedJavaObjects[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m` in their ParseContext or TikaConfig, acknowledging [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe security implications.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Future enhancement: implement a strict whitelist-based `ObjectInputFilter` to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallow safe classes only, reducing the need for a full disable.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. No Harness or Test Code Changes  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – All modifications are confined to `RTFParser` and `RTFEmbObjHandler`.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Fuzz harness and existing test code remain unchanged, making this patch [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtransparent to existing CI and fuzz targets.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Reference Patterns  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Similar flag-based disablement appears in other Tika parsers [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., disabling [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39membedded scripts in HTML[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – When ObjectInputFilter is eventually adopted, it will mirror the approach used[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the Apache POI project to sandbox OLE-item deserialization.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempt adds a new boolean flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`allowEmbeddedJavaObjects`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to RTFParser[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand propagates it into RTFEmbObjHandler. In RTFEmbObjHandler a corresponding field [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`allowJavaDeserialization`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and constructor parameter were introduced, and the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode path for EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA was wrapped in an `if` that records a security[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception if deserialization is disabled.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the Microsoft parser module fails to compile with dozens [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof “illegal start of type,” “identifier expected,” and “reached end of file while [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing” errors in RTFEmbObjHandler.java and RTFParser.java.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • A Jazzer-based fuzz test triggers a stack trace rooted in [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The exception is `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRemote Code Execution` indicating that untrusted data can drive `new [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The call chain goes through RTFParser → TextExtractor → RTFEmbObjHandler → [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mObjectInputStream, demonstrating a genuine deserialization vector in RTF parsing.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. RTFParser.java modifications  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added a new private boolean field:  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + `@Field private boolean allowEmbeddedJavaObjects = false;`  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Updated the parser invocation:  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Changed the instantiation of `RTFEmbObjHandler` in `[0m[1;35mparseInline[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minclude the new flag:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `new [0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler[0m[1;39m([0m[39mhandler, metadata, context, [0m[1;35mgetMemoryLimitInKb[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowEmbeddedJavaObjects[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added bean-style setter and getter for the flag:  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + `public void [0m[1;35msetAllowEmbeddedJavaObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + `public boolean [0m[1;35mgetAllowEmbeddedJavaObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. RTFEmbObjHandler.java modifications  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introduced a constructor parameter and corresponding field:  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + `private final boolean allowJavaDeserialization;`  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wrapped the existing deserialization branch:  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • If `!allowJavaDeserialization`, record a `TikaException` via [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mEmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Else proceed with the original `new [0m[1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdownstream logic.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Post-Patch Build Output  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The Microsoft parser module fails to compile. Key errors include:  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – “illegal start of type” and “<identifier> expected” at the top of [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRTFEmbObjHandler.java.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – “reached end of file while parsing” indicating unmatched braces.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Similar syntax errors in RTFParser.java around the new constructor calls and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield definitions.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Maven reports [0m[1;36m46[0m[39m compilation errors in the tika-parser-microsoft-module.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • RTFEmbObjHandler.java file structure  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Verify `package` declaration and `import` blocks aren’t broken by the patch.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Ensure the new constructor signature and field declarations are placed [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin the class body and that matching braces remain in place.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • RTFParser.java edits  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Confirm the `parseInline` method signature and instantiation site match [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting indentation and brace scope.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Check that `@Field` annotations on new members are imported and [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msyntactically valid.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • EMB_STATE enum and state-handling code in RTFEmbObjHandler  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Review surrounding code for correct block scoping around the new `if/else` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand exception-recording logic.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Build configuration  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Ensure there are no leftover merge conflicts or truncations in patched files[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat could cause parse errors.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
